node.text:
During my isolation it was tough not being able to gym, but had to find the motivation to get some type of sweat in so I came up with a few workouts, so here’s a good one! try this if you’re stuck in the house or if your gym isn’t open!

-30 sec jump rope
-30 sec in and out squat jumps
-30 sec RDL to squat
-30 sec lunge up jumps
-30 sec alt side plank twists

Wearing my own @get_tighterr sweat belt to make me feel tight and to sweat a little extra durning my HIIT workouts 😁 you can pre order yours with the link in my bio! 
Sizes S-XXL (true to size)
I’m wearing a medium

node.text:
So excited to be teaming up with @get_tighterr and coming out with my own logo sweat belt!!!

If you see my stories often, you see me using this everyday pretty much during cardio workout or high intensity to help with the jiggle or just to help sweat a little extra. 

If you’d like to support and get yourself one they are now available to pre order!! If you order now or before April 25th you’ll be able with to save money 😁

https://www.tighterr.com/products/getfitwjessica-series-sweat-belt or link in bio! ❤️

node.text:
Thank you to everyone for your prayers.

Yesterday, my sister, brother and I gained a guardian angel. My mom held on as long as she could and her heart couldn’t take it anymore..

I’ve never felt this pain in my entire life, my heart aches and is broken in so many pieces. I’m speechless. All of this was so unexpected. I was just having a conversation with her last week and I didn’t ever think that was going to be my last time getting to hear her voice. Covid took my mom and I can’t wrap my head around it. I am so hurt and my heart is so heavy

I’m living a nightmare, my life will never be the same, she was my biggest supporter, my go to, my hype man, the best mom I could ask for. I know she and my dad will always be watching over, my 2 guardian angles, im going to love and miss forever💔😢

node.text:
This is my mom.. she is mentally the strongest person I know. Definitely where I get my mental strength from.🙏🏽
She’s watched my dads cancer journey (when i was a baby) which a few year later he had passed (not from cancer) she watched her almost fiancées cancer journey (that took his life) she watched her youngest child’s cancer journey (me) and she never lost faith or hope..

A little over a week ago she tested positive for covid and in Wednesday morning she had to go to the hospital.

She was on a bi-Papp machine for 2 days and when her oxygen level wasn’t passing 70 and her blood oxygen was at a level 30,  they decided that it was best for her to go on a ventilator last night.

Her oxygen level was starting at a level 70 at midnight and slowly made its way up to 90 this morning. By tonight it’s at a 96 which is great news since that’s a response to treatment. She will be going into the ICU when they have a room available for her but right now she’s getting cared for as if she was in the ICU. 

Today my brother, sister and I were able to go and see her, and talk to her which I have to say was the most traumatizing and heart breaking experience I’ve went through. I am now seeing how real and scary this situation is.

 I seriously pray for all the families that have to deal with this. I don’t wish this on anyone. I’ve never felt so much pain and I can’t wait for the second she wakes up from this mess.

Bless you all for the continuous prayers 🙏🏽
